---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Inflation vs. Savings: Calculating Your Real Return",
    "description": "Understand the difference between nominal and real returns. Use our calculator to see how inflation and taxes erode your cash savings.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Fire Maths"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a real return?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A real return is your investment's yield after accounting for inflation. If you earn 5% interest, but inflation is 3%, your 'nominal' return is 5%, but your 'real' return is only roughly 2%."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why am I losing money in a savings account?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Even if your balance goes up, your purchasing power might go down. If your after-tax interest rate is lower than the inflation rate, your money is effectively shrinking in value."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do taxes affect savings?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Interest earned in standard bank accounts is taxed as ordinary income at your marginal rate. This means a 5% gross interest rate might actually be a 3.5% net interest rate after taxes are applied."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<SiteLayout site="firemaths" title="Inflation vs. Savings: Calculate Your Real Return" description="Discover the true cost of holding cash. Compare inflation vs savings rates and calculate your after-tax real return on your emergency fund." canonical="https://firemaths.info/inflation-vs-savings" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Inflation vs. Savings</h1>
      <p>The Silent Killer of Purchasing Power</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <p>A bank offering 5% interest on a savings account sounds fantastic until you remember the two guarantees in life: death and taxes. In the financial world, we must add a third: <strong>inflation</strong>. To understand if your cash is actually growing, you must calculate your "Real Return" after accounting for both taxes and the declining value of money.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Nominal vs. Real Returns</h2>
    <p>When a bank advertises an interest rate, they are stating the <strong>Nominal Rate</strong>. This is the raw percentage your money will grow. If you put $1,000 in a 5% account, you will have $1,050 next year.</p>
    <p>But what if the cost of groceries, rent, and gas went up by 4% during that same year? It now costs $1,040 to buy what used to cost $1,000. Your $50 gain is mostly wiped out by increased costs.</p>
    <p>The <strong>Real Return</strong> is the nominal return minus the inflation rate. In this example, your real return is roughly 1%.</p>

    <h2>The Impact of Taxes</h2>
    <p>Unfortunately, the math gets worse. The government taxes you on your <em>nominal</em> return, not your real return.</p>
    <p>If you earn 5% interest in a non-registered account, and your marginal tax rate is 30%, you lose 1.5% to taxes. Your after-tax nominal return is now 3.5%. If inflation is 4%, your after-tax real return is <strong>-0.5%</strong>. You are literally losing purchasing power by keeping your money in the bank.</p>

    <h2>Calculate Your Real Return</h2>
    <div class="card" id="calculator-container">
      <div class="calc-grid">
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="interestRate">Advertised Interest Rate (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="interestRate" value="4.50" step="0.1" min="0" />
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="inflationRate">Current Inflation Rate (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="inflationRate" value="3.00" step="0.1" min="0" />
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="taxRate">Marginal Tax Rate (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="taxRate" value="30.00" step="1" min="0" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <button id="calculateBtn" class="calc-btn">Calculate Real Return</button>

      <div id="results" class="results-container" style="display: none;">
        <div class="summary-box">
          <p><strong>Gross Interest Rate:</strong> <span id="resGross"></span>%</p>
          <p><strong>Taxes Paid:</strong> <span id="resTax"></span>%</p>
          <p><strong>Net (After-Tax) Rate:</strong> <span id="resNet"></span>%</p>
          <hr style="border-color: var(--border-color); margin: 10px 0;" />
          <p style="color: var(--text-secondary);"><strong>Minus Inflation:</strong> <span id="resInf"></span>%</p>
          <h3 style="margin-top: 10px; color: var(--accent-color);">Real Purchasing Power Return: <span id="resReal"></span>%</h3>
        </div>
        <p id="analysisText" style="margin-top: 1rem;"></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>How to Protect Your Cash</h2>
    <p>If holding cash often results in a negative real return, what should a FIRE practitioner do?</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Minimize Cash Holdings:</strong> Keep your cash <a href="/emergency-fund-where">emergency fund</a> strictly limited to what you actually need (3-6 months), and invest the rest in appreciating assets like equities or real estate.</li>
      <li><strong>Use Tax-Advantaged Accounts:</strong> Hold your cash or <a href="/money-market-funds-guide">Money Market Funds</a> inside a TFSA or Roth IRA to eliminate the tax drag, improving your real return.</li>
      <li><strong>Lock in Peak Rates:</strong> When interest rates are high but inflation begins to drop, build a <a href="/gic-ladder-calculator">GIC Ladder</a> to lock in the high nominal rates for the next 3-5 years.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For a complete breakdown of all your cash options, read our overarching guide: <a href="/cash-savings-compared">Cash Savings Compared</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const calcBtn = document.getElementById('calculateBtn');

      calcBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const interestRate = parseFloat(document.getElementById('interestRate').value);
        const inflationRate = parseFloat(document.getElementById('inflationRate').value);
        const taxRate = parseFloat(document.getElementById('taxRate').value);

        if (isNaN(interestRate) || isNaN(inflationRate) || isNaN(taxRate)) {
          alert("Please enter valid numbers.");
          return;
        }

        const taxDrag = interestRate * (taxRate / 100);
        const netRate = interestRate - taxDrag;
        const realReturn = netRate - inflationRate;

        document.getElementById('resGross').innerText = interestRate.toFixed(2);
        document.getElementById('resTax').innerText = taxDrag.toFixed(2);
        document.getElementById('resNet').innerText = netRate.toFixed(2);
        document.getElementById('resInf').innerText = inflationRate.toFixed(2);

        const realSpan = document.getElementById('resReal');
        realSpan.innerText = realReturn.toFixed(2);
        realSpan.style.color = realReturn >= 0 ? '#4ade80' : '#f87171'; // Green if positive, Red if negative

        const analysisText = document.getElementById('analysisText');
        if (realReturn > 0) {
          analysisText.innerHTML = "Great! Your savings are currently outpacing both taxes and inflation. You are growing real wealth.";
        } else if (realReturn === 0) {
          analysisText.innerHTML = "You are exactly breaking even. Your purchasing power is being preserved, but not grown.";
        } else {
          analysisText.innerHTML = "<strong>Warning:</strong> You are losing purchasing power. Your after-tax interest is not enough to keep up with the rising cost of living. Keep your cash buffer, but ensure your long-term wealth is invested in equities or real estate.";
        }

        document.getElementById('results').style.display = 'block';
      });
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    h2 { margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    p { margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    ul { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    /* Calculator Styles */
    .calc-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .input-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
    .input-group label { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.9rem; }
    .input-group input { padding: 0.75rem; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 8px; background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--card-bg) 50%, transparent); color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1rem; }

    .calc-btn { width: 100%; padding: 1rem; background: var(--accent-color); color: #fff; border: none; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; transition: opacity 0.2s; }
    .calc-btn:hover { opacity: 0.9; }

    .results-container { margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-top: 1.5rem; }
    .summary-box { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--card-bg) 80%, transparent); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .summary-box p { margin: 0.5rem 0; color: var(--text-primary); display: flex; justify-content: space-between; font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .summary-box h3 { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
